shanty
Homonym Number: 1
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:2
Definition:(formerly) a rough, country inn, or a place selling sly grog.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: >1875. `Spectator' (Melbourne), June 26, p. 91, col. I
